Package: LRMoE
Type: Package
Title: LRMoE for actuarial loss modelling
Version: 0.1.1
Date: 2020-07-13
Author: Spark Tseung [aut, cre],
  Tsz Chai Fung [aut],
  Andrei L. Badescu [aut],
  Sheldon X. Lin [aut]
Maintainer: Spark Tseung <spark.tseung@mail.utoronto.ca>
Description: This package is based on the Logit-Weighted Reduced Mixture-of-Experts (LRMoE) 
  proposed by Fung et al. (2019), which is a flexible framework actuarial loss modelling.
  For more details, see Fung et al. (2019) "A class of mixture of experts models for general insurance: Theoretical developments"
  published in Insurance: Mathematics and Economics, and
  Fung et al. (2019) "A CLASS OF MIXTURE OF EXPERTS MODELS FOR GENERAL INSURANCE: APPLICATION TO CORRELATED CLAIM FREQUENCIES"
  in ASTIN Bulletin: The Journal of the IAA.
License: GPL-3
URL: https://github.com/sparktseung/LRMoE
BugReports: https://github.com/sparktseung/LRMoE/issues
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: false
Depends: R (>= 3.5)
Imports:
  actuar,
  copula,
  expint,
  EnvStats,
  ggplot2,
  matrixStats,
  NMOF,
